set_proto_mod...cal_constraint(25.10)    set_proto_mod...cal_constraint(25.10)

Name
       set_proto_model_physical_constraint - Sets FlexModels to specific phys-
       ical constraints to guide placement

Syntax
       set_proto_model_physical_constraint

       [-help]

       -type {guide | fence | region | soft_guide | none}

       [-model <string>]

       Sets FlexModels to specific physical constraints to guide placement. By
       default, all the FlexModels will be set to the specified type.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -modelstring
              Specifies a list of flexmodels.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type {guide | fence | region | soft_guide | none}
              Specifies the constraint type. You can select one of the follow-
              ing options:

              * guide

              * fence

              * region

              * soft_guide

              * none

              Data_type: enum, required

Examples
       The  following commands change physical constraint of all FlexModels to
       guide before running detailed placement:

       set_proto_model_physical_constraint -type guide

        set_proto_mode -effort high

       place_opt_design

       earlyGlobalRoute

       timeDesign -proto

       load_timing_debug_report -proto

Related Information
